The paper deals with device to device communication and the use of Software Defined Networking (SDN) to manage data flows among devices. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category. Additionally, the paper focuses on using Machine Learning techniques to infer the number of nodes actively involved in receiving data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. The use of SDN also suggests that the paper may belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category. The paper also deals with the security of communication protocols, which suggests that it may belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the use of Machine Learning techniques to infer information about the network suggests that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category.
